bevyengine/bevy#21949.body:
## What you did

I backported the new automatic directional navigation graph from `main` into a Bevy 0.14.2 project to add controller / focus navigation.

The code I ported includes the `DirectionalNavigationPlugin` and the `auto_rebuild_ui_navigation_graph` system, which rebuilds the `DirectionalNavigationMap` whenever any `AutoDirectionalNavigation` UI node changes.

## What went wrong

### What I was expecting

Every time `auto_rebuild_ui_navigation_graph` runs, I expected the `DirectionalNavigationMap` to represent only the current set of focusable nodes and edges, with no references to removed UI elements.

### What actually happened

Because `auto_rebuild_ui_navigation_graph` does not clear the map before calling `auto_generate_navigation_edges`, old entries remain in `DirectionalNavigationMap.neighbors`:
- The map retains neighbors that point to entities that no longer exist or no longer have `AutoDirectionalNavigation`.

In my backport, I fixed this by explicitly clearing the map before rebuilding:

```rust
fn auto_rebuild_ui_navigation_graph(
    mut directional_navigation_map: ResMut<DirectionalNavigationMap>,
    config: Res<AutoNavigationConfig>,
    changed_nodes: Query< /* ... */ >,
    all_nodes: Query< /* ... */ >,
) {
    if changed_nodes.is_empty() {
        return;
    }

    let nodes: Vec<FocusableArea> = /* build nodes from all_nodes */;

    // Fix: clear the old graph before regenerating
    directional_navigation_map.clear();
    auto_generate_navigation_edges(&mut directional_navigation_map, &nodes, &config);
}

