    ));
}

fn send_event_every_second(query: Query<Entity, With<MyEntity>>, mut commands: Commands) {
    for entity in query.iter() {
        commands.trigger(MyEvent(entity));
        info!("Sent MyEvent to entity {:?}", entity);
    }
}
```

## What went wrong

I expected the string within the closure to be the same as outside, i.e. "Hello, Bevy!".
But the string inside the closure are always random bytes.
Sometimes part of the real string, sometimes random string, sometimes the program panics with "invalid value for char"

Output of some example runs of the reproduction code above:
```
2025-12-16T16:27:29.314699Z  INFO bevy_winit::system: Creating new window minimal_repro (0v0)
2025-12-16T16:27:29.386622Z  INFO minimal_repro: Dynamic string before closure: 'Hello, Bevy!'
2025-12-16T16:27:30.391179Z  INFO minimal_repro: Sent MyEvent to entity 12v0
2025-12-16T16:27:30.391355Z  INFO minimal_repro: Dynamic string inside closure: 'copy_bind_gr'
```

```
2025-12-16T16:26:27.367681Z  INFO bevy_winit::system: Creating new window minimal_repro (0v0)
2025-12-16T16:26:27.427773Z  INFO minimal_repro: Dynamic string before closure: 'Hello, Bevy!'
2025-12-16T16:26:28.431345Z  INFO minimal_repro: Sent MyEvent to entity 12v0
2025-12-16T16:26:28.431545Z  INFO minimal_repro: Dynamic string inside closure: '☻☺'
```

Also despawning this observer sometimes results in a heap corruption panic.

## Additional information

I guess there is a memory leak within the observer function in combination with a move closure.

Without the move keyword the program (correctly) won't compile, even if the value is cloned inside the closure:
```
error[E0373]: closure may outlive the current function, but it borrows `dynamic_string`, which is owned by the current function
  --> minimal_repro\src\main.rs:28:17
   |
28 |         observe(|_trigger: On<MyEvent>| {
   |                 ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ may outlive borrowed value `dynamic_string`
29 |             let inside_string = dynamic_string.clone();
   |                                 -------------- `dynamic_string` is borrowed here
   |
```

